   Computer and information technology products and services through FAST
   is easier, better, faster, cheaper, and smarter!
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   What is the purpose of FAST ?

   In today's FAST paced information and computer age, relying on quality
   computer and information technology products and services is essential
   for all government agencies. Typical equipment and services include
   Automated Data Processing (ADP) equipment; all computer hardware and
   software; information systems integration; computer operating and
   office systems; Internet products, servers and network equipment;
   minicomputers, UNIX systems; all Microsoft products; workstations; LAN
   and WAN equipment including cable and wiring; computer user training;
   telecommunications equipment; and associated information technology
   services and systems maintenance and installation.

   The GSA Region 2 FTS FAST programs central goal is to fully serve all
   government customer needs. Our purpose is to provide ADP computer
   equipment, hardware and software at the best value to the Government
   with minimal acquisition lead-time and delivery. The FAST program has a
   national scope and is being administered by the GSA Office of
   Information Technology Integration (ITI).

   To help meet your computer and information technology requirements, GSA
   Region 2 FTS' FAST program meets your federal agency needs for quality
   information technology solutions. Tell a FAST account manager what you
   want, and we do the rest!

   What is Region 2 FTS's mission through FAST ?

   GSA Region 2 FTS will participate in any new iterations of applications
   or tools which will optimize the FAST program processes. As new program
   processes with direct or indirect impacts on improving procurement and
   acquisition and/or customer service evolve, Region 2 FTS FAST intends
   to implement those improvements. Promise of the FAST programs future
   success hinges on consistent vigilance toward improved procurement and
   customer service. As a result, this vigilance will dictate the efforts
   of the GSA FAST program to exercise continuous process and procedural
   improvements. Our business is to provide information technology
   solutions and network services that deliver best value and innovation
   to support our customers missions worldwide.

   What can we do for you ?

   The FAST program operated by the GSA Region 2 FTS has overcome the
   inherent risks of establishing a new business line. FAST has an
   established, highly satisfied federal customer base and is operating on
   a sound financial basis. GSA FAST has established access to multiple
   sources of supply, and it's experienced procurement staff is capable of
   delivering timely, cost-effective computer and information technology
   equipment and services, while adjusting to fluctuations of demand.

   How does FAST procurement of computers, hardware, software, COTS, etc.
   work ?

   Located in New York, the GSA Region 2 FTS FAST program provides
   military and civilian government agencies with comprehensive expertise
   and assistance in procurement and acquisition of computer and
   information technology equipment and services. Our skilled staff
   specializes in acquiring technical equipment and services, and FAST is
   dedicated to providing your government agency with the overall best
   value for your money.

   How does the acquisition of LAN's, WAN's, servers, networking products,
   and operating systems work ?

   GSA FAST account managers negotiate with reputable computer and
   information technology suppliers. FAST then uses a variety of
   procurement vehicles, methods and sources to deliver computer products
   and services to your federal government agency. Whether under GSA
   Schedule Contracts, Definite Quantity Contracts, Indefinite Delivery
   Contracts, or GSA Multiple Award Schedule Contracts, FAST can provide
   the highest quality computer and information technology products,
   premier services, and the fastest delivery schedules available.
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

                    What other services does FAST provide ?
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   FAST also provides system integration and ADP services, and internet
   equipment. GSA can also integrate the FAST program with other
   information technology programs such as the Federal Information Systems
   Support Program (FISSP), Non-FISSP Services, as well as other related
   information technology services. This integration works to provide
   recurring services, systems development, information systems
   operations, studies, and other related ADP support

